1
00:00:03,046 --> 00:00:05,6
("Ain't No Rest for the Wicked"
by Cage the Elephant playing)

2
00:00:12,093 --> 00:00:14,4
♪ I was walking
down the street ♪

3
00:00:14,064 --> 00:00:16,1
♪ When out the corner
of my eye ♪

4
00:00:16,030 --> 00:00:19,1
♪ I saw a pretty little thing
approaching me ♪

5
00:00:19,035 --> 00:00:21,2
♪ She said,
"I never seen a man ♪

6
00:00:21,048 --> 00:00:23,1
♪ "Who looked so all alone ♪

7
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:25,4
♪ Oh, could you use
a little company?" ♪

8
00:00:25,069 --> 00:00:28,3
♪ Not even 15 minutes later, I'm
still walking down the street ♪

9
00:00:28,053 --> 00:00:31,3
♪ When I saw the shadow of a man
creep out of sight ♪

10
00:00:31,053 --> 00:00:33,2
♪ And then he swept up
from behind ♪

11
00:00:33,045 --> 00:00:35,0
♪ He put a gun up to my head ♪

12
00:00:35,028 --> 00:00:37,1
♪ He made it clear he wasn't
looking for a fight ♪

13
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:38,8
♪ He said,
"Give me all you got ♪

14
00:00:39,004 --> 00:00:41,2
♪ "I want your money,
not your life ♪

15
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,1
♪ But if you try to make a move,
I won't think twice" ♪
(siren wailing)

16
00:00:44,037 --> 00:00:45,7
♪ I told him,
"You can have my cash ♪

17
00:00:45,092 --> 00:00:47,7
♪ "But first you know
I got to ask ♪

18
00:00:47,092 --> 00:00:49,4
♪ What made you want to live
this kind of life?" ♪

19
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:52,8
♪ He said there ain't no rest
for the wicked ♪

20
00:00:53,001 --> 00:00:55,6
♪ Money don't grow on trees ♪

21
00:00:55,084 --> 00:00:57,9
♪ I got bills to pay,
I got mouths to feed ♪

22
00:00:58,014 --> 00:00:59,8
Turn the music
down, sir.

23
00:01:00,006 --> 00:01:01,1
♪ There ain't nothing
in this world for free... ♪

24
00:01:01,039 --> 00:01:03,7
Hey, cut the music.

25
00:01:03,094 --> 00:01:05,3
(chuckling):
I'm sorry.

26
00:01:05,052 --> 00:01:06,6
(music volume decreases)

27
00:01:06,090 --> 00:01:08,3
You know why I pulled you over?

28
00:01:08,057 --> 00:01:10,8
Well, obviously, you felt
the need to exercise

29
00:01:11,007 --> 00:01:12,4
your limited powers
and punish me

30
00:01:12,069 --> 00:01:13,9
for ignoring
the speed limit.

31
00:01:14,020 --> 00:01:16,3
It's okay. I understand.

32
00:01:16,053 --> 00:01:18,6
I-I like to punish people, too.

33
00:01:18,087 --> 00:01:20,2
Or at least I used to.

34
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:22,5
License and
registration.

35
00:01:22,075 --> 00:01:24,3
(sighs)
Coming right up.

36
00:01:24,058 --> 00:01:26,0
♪ Man creep out of sight ♪

37
00:01:26,021 --> 00:01:27,5
♪ And then he swept up... ♪

38
00:01:27,075 --> 00:01:29,9
Are you trying
to bribe me, sir?

39
00:01:30,013 --> 00:01:31,5
Yes, of course.

40
00:01:31,071 --> 00:01:34,2
♪ He said,
"Give me all you got..." ♪

41
00:01:34,042 --> 00:01:35,3
Is that not enough?

42
00:01:35,059 --> 00:01:37,3
Take more. It's only money.

43
00:01:37,059 --> 00:01:39,3
It's against
the law, sir.

44
00:01:39,051 --> 00:01:40,8
(chuckles) You people are funny
about your laws, aren't you?

45
00:01:42,052 --> 00:01:45,9
You break the law sometimes,
don't you?

46
00:01:46,010 --> 00:01:48,2
♪ I said, "You're such
a sweet young thing..." ♪

47
00:01:48,048 --> 00:01:49,9
Sometimes...

48
00:01:50,015 --> 00:01:51,9
I put my siren on
and drive really fast

49
00:01:52,011 --> 00:01:53,5
for no reason at all,

50
00:01:53,078 --> 00:01:55,0
just 'cause I can.

51
00:01:55,028 --> 00:01:56,3
Right?

52
00:01:56,053 --> 00:01:58,2
And why wouldn't you? It's fun.

53
00:01:58,045 --> 00:02:00,0
It feels good to get away
with something, doesn't it?

54
00:02:00,028 --> 00:02:02,0
Yeah.

55
00:02:03,091 --> 00:02:05,8
Uh, it's okay,
Officer.

56
00:02:06,008 --> 00:02:07,7
People like to tell me things,

57
00:02:07,092 --> 00:02:11,4
those deep, dark, naughty little
desires that are on their mind.

58
00:02:11,063 --> 00:02:12,7
It's a gift.

59
00:02:12,096 --> 00:02:14,9
Must be something
about this face.

60
00:02:16,072 --> 00:02:17,8
You're tempted
to keep that, aren't you?

61
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:20,1
Well, what are you
waiting for, permission?

62
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,0
Go on, take it, buy yourself
something pretty.

63
00:02:22,026 --> 00:02:23,1
You deserve it.

64
00:02:25,014 --> 00:02:27,7
But if you don't mind,
I really must be on my way.

65
00:02:27,094 --> 00:02:29,4
Oh, yeah, of course.

66
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:31,7
Hey, have a nice evening.

67
00:02:31,098 --> 00:02:34,6
You, too, Officer.

68
00:02:34,086 --> 00:02:36,6
You, too.
(music volume increases)

69
00:02:36,086 --> 00:02:38,9
♪ "You can have my cash, but
first you know I got to ask ♪

70
00:02:39,011 --> 00:02:41,7
♪ What made you want to live
this kind of life?" ♪

71
00:02:41,095 --> 00:02:45,4
♪ He said there ain't no rest
for the wicked ♪

72
00:02:45,062 --> 00:02:47,7
♪ Money don't grow on trees ♪

73
00:02:47,096 --> 00:02:51,0
♪ I got bills to pay,
I got mouths to feed ♪

74
00:02:51,029 --> 00:02:54,0
♪ There ain't nothing
in this world for free ♪

75
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:58,0
♪ Oh, no, there ain't
no rest for the wicked ♪

76
00:02:58,022 --> 00:03:00,1
♪ - Until we close
our eyes for good. ♪
- Hey, boss.

77
00:03:00,034 --> 00:03:03,1
("Fame" by David Bowie playing)

78
00:03:09,089 --> 00:03:15,1
♪ Fame makes a man
take things over ♪

79
00:03:15,032 --> 00:03:20,6
♪ Fame lets him loose,
hard to swallow ♪

80
00:03:20,086 --> 00:03:25,6
♪ Fame puts you there
where things are hollow ♪

81
00:03:25,087 --> 00:03:28,0
♪ Fame... ♪

82
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:30,0
Where have you been?

83
00:03:30,021 --> 00:03:31,6
Oh, holed up
in a château,

84
00:03:31,088 --> 00:03:33,7
copulating with a young
woman named Faith.

85
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,1
It's ironic, isn't it?

86
00:03:35,038 --> 00:03:38,3
Thank you, Patrick.
You can go.

87
00:03:41,038 --> 00:03:42,5
(chuckles)

88
00:03:42,076 --> 00:03:44,0
You little devil.

89
00:03:44,026 --> 00:03:45,1
What?

90
00:03:45,031 --> 00:03:46,8
I dropped something.

91
00:03:47,006 --> 00:03:48,5
Well, I'm sure you did.

92
00:03:48,073 --> 00:03:51,3
Now, Lucifer,
I am a big fan of sex.

93
00:03:51,052 --> 00:03:52,7
Obviously.

94
00:03:52,098 --> 00:03:55,5
But I didn't leave Hell
to be a bartender.

95
00:03:55,073 --> 00:03:57,5
Shouldn't you be spending
your valuable time

96
00:03:57,073 --> 00:04:00,8
doing something
more significant?

97
00:04:01,003 --> 00:04:02,5
(scoffs)

98
00:04:02,074 --> 00:04:04,8
You're the lord of Hell,
for crying out loud.

99
00:04:05,003 --> 00:04:07,1
I am retired, Maze.
I've got nothing but time.

100
00:04:07,037 --> 00:04:08,4
Thank you.

101
00:04:12,033 --> 00:04:14,2
(music plays in slow motion)

102
00:04:18,017 --> 00:04:21,2
(echoing):
♪ Fame, fame... ♪

103
00:04:21,042 --> 00:04:23,7
I think you have a visitor.

104
00:04:30,031 --> 00:04:31,6
(sighs)

105
00:04:31,085 --> 00:04:33,3
Amenadiel,
how's it hanging, big guy?

106
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:35,1
Huh?

107
00:04:35,031 --> 00:04:38,7
Your return to the Underworld
has been requested.

108
00:04:38,094 --> 00:04:40,4
Oh, right, okay.

109
00:04:40,065 --> 00:04:42,1
Let me just, uh,
check my calendar.

110
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,9
Yeah, here it is.

111
00:04:44,016 --> 00:04:45,9
Uh, the seventh of never

112
00:04:46,016 --> 00:04:47,8
through to the 15th
of ain't-gonna-happen.

113
00:04:48,008 --> 00:04:49,4
How does that work
for you guys?

114
00:04:49,062 --> 00:04:51,0
(sighs)

115
00:04:51,029 --> 00:04:53,2
Look, remind Dad
that I quit Hell

116
00:04:53,046 --> 00:04:55,9
because I was sick and tired
of playing a part in his play.

117
00:04:56,017 --> 00:04:57,4
I'm gonna warn you

118
00:04:57,063 --> 00:04:58,9
against disrespecting
our father, Lucifer.

119
00:04:59,013 --> 00:05:00,4
Yeah, well, our father's
been disrespecting me

120
00:05:00,063 --> 00:05:01,5
since the beginning of time,

121
00:05:01,071 --> 00:05:04,2
so pot-kettle, don't you think?

122
00:05:04,047 --> 00:05:07,9
You are a mockery of
everything divine.

123
00:05:08,014 --> 00:05:09,7
Thank you.

124
00:05:09,097 --> 00:05:12,7
Thank you, but lately I've been
doing a fair amount of thinking.

125
00:05:12,098 --> 00:05:14,7
Now, do you think
I'm the Devil

126
00:05:14,098 --> 00:05:16,2
because I'm inherently evil,

127
00:05:16,048 --> 00:05:18,7
just because dear old Dad
decided I was?

128
00:05:18,098 --> 00:05:19,9
What exactly do
you think happens

129
00:05:20,015 --> 00:05:20,9
when the Devil
leaves Hell?

130
00:05:21,015 --> 00:05:23,4
(scoffs)

131
00:05:23,061 --> 00:05:24,9
All of those demons,

132
00:05:25,011 --> 00:05:27,4
all of those tormented
and tortured souls,

133
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:29,4
where do you think they go?

134
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:32,7
Don't know, don't care.

135
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,0
Not my problem, brother.

136
00:05:34,029 --> 00:05:37,0
So consider the position
officially open.

137
00:05:38,075 --> 00:05:40,4
And you, my feathered friend,
can go to Hell.

138
00:05:42,055 --> 00:05:43,6
(chuckles)

139
00:05:43,084 --> 00:05:46,1
Yeah, try it.

140
00:05:46,034 --> 00:05:48,6
You think Father's upset now.

141
00:05:48,085 --> 00:05:50,3
(chuckles)

142
00:05:53,064 --> 00:05:57,7
You know, he will not be
merciful for much longer.

143
00:06:04,061 --> 00:06:06,4
(music resumes at normal tempo)

144
00:06:17,062 --> 00:06:19,1
Hey, you.

145
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:20,6
Remember me?

146
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:23,1
You're famous, aren't you?
GIRL: Delilah!

147
00:06:23,038 --> 00:06:24,8
LUCIFER: Delilah, isn't it?
GIRL: I love you, Delilah!

148
00:06:26,047 --> 00:06:27,6
Can I have your autograph?

149
00:06:27,088 --> 00:06:30,1
(chuckles)
If I can have a drink.

150
00:06:30,039 --> 00:06:32,6
LUCIFER: So are you gonna tell
me why you really came back?

151
00:06:32,089 --> 00:06:34,7
There's something
I need to know.

152
00:06:34,097 --> 00:06:36,3
And what's that?

153
00:06:36,056 --> 00:06:40,3
Did I... sell my soul
to the Devil?

154
00:06:40,056 --> 00:06:42,3
(chuckles)
Well, that would imply

155
00:06:42,057 --> 00:06:43,8
the Devil's actually
interested in your soul.

156
00:06:44,007 --> 00:06:47,2
Look, all I did
was introduce you

157
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,7
to a few key people who
owed me favors, that's all.

158
00:06:49,091 --> 00:06:52,8
I mean, with all the good
came a hell of a lot of bad.

159
00:06:53,008 --> 00:06:55,5
Oh, right, so the Devil
made you do it, did he?

160
00:06:55,075 --> 00:06:57,8
The alcohol and the drugs,
the topless selfies.

161
00:06:58,008 --> 00:06:59,6
The choices are
on you, my dear.

162
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:01,5
I mean, Jimmy Barnes?

163
00:07:01,075 --> 00:07:04,2
I can't believe you almost
married that sweaty little imp.

164
00:07:04,046 --> 00:07:05,2
He produced my album.

165
00:07:05,046 --> 00:07:06,9
You introduced me to him.

166
00:07:07,017 --> 00:07:08,7
I suggested you work with him,
not sleep with him.

167
00:07:08,093 --> 00:07:10,3
Well, I got confused.

168
00:07:10,055 --> 00:07:11,4
And then you left him
at the altar.

169
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:12,9
Yeah, that was rude of me.

170
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:13,9
No, actually, I quite
enjoyed that bit.

171
00:07:14,018 --> 00:07:15,6
(both chuckle)

172
00:07:15,085 --> 00:07:17,6
You know, he trapped me
in the bathroom at the Grammys,

173
00:07:17,085 --> 00:07:18,8
said he wanted
to get back together.

174
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:19,9
Then I hear he's marrying

175
00:07:20,019 --> 00:07:21,5
a supermodel--
this weekend.

176
00:07:21,077 --> 00:07:23,1
And I'm jealous.

177
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,8
Oh, God, I'm a mess.

178
00:07:26,007 --> 00:07:27,9
God has nothing to
do with your mess.

179
00:07:28,011 --> 00:07:29,5
Look...

180
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:33,9
You didn't sell
your soul, Delilah.

181
00:07:34,012 --> 00:07:35,3
You do owe me a favor.

182
00:07:35,058 --> 00:07:37,0
I'm scared.

183
00:07:37,029 --> 00:07:38,5
You should be.

184
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:39,9
Because what
I'm about to ask you

185
00:07:40,012 --> 00:07:41,2
is gonna be
quite difficult for you.

186
00:07:42,092 --> 00:07:44,7
Pull yourself together.

187
00:07:44,096 --> 00:07:47,5
That's it, that's
all I'm asking.

188
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:50,6
'Cause you're wasting
your talent, your life.

189
00:07:50,088 --> 00:07:52,9
Hmm?

190
00:07:55,026 --> 00:07:57,7
You're human, darling.
(chuckles)

191
00:07:57,097 --> 00:08:00,0
I'm gonna do
as you asked.

192
00:08:00,023 --> 00:08:02,3
I'm gonna get
it together.

193
00:08:02,056 --> 00:08:04,6
Promise, Lucifer.

194
00:08:04,081 --> 00:08:06,6
Look, it's not about me.

195
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:10,1
What happens now,
that's up to you.

196
00:08:10,032 --> 00:08:12,4
- Okay?
- Yeah.

197
00:08:12,061 --> 00:08:13,7
Come here, you.

198
00:08:16,095 --> 00:08:17,9
(tires squealing)

199
00:08:32,097 --> 00:08:34,8
(gasps)

200
00:08:55,016 --> 00:08:56,8
Oh, no, no, no, not yet.

201
00:08:57,003 --> 00:08:58,7
(gasps)

202
00:08:58,095 --> 00:08:59,9
What did you do?

203
00:09:00,020 --> 00:09:01,4
I'm sorry.

204
00:09:01,066 --> 00:09:03,5
"Sorry."

205
00:09:03,075 --> 00:09:05,6
Why did you end her life?

206
00:09:05,088 --> 00:09:07,6
Why else?

207
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:09,0
Money.

208
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:11,0
"Money."

209
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:14,5
Oh, it's times like this
I wish I was still in Hell.

210
00:09:14,072 --> 00:09:17,8
All the fun activities
I'd have planned for you.

211
00:09:18,005 --> 00:09:20,2
Hey, man, I just
pulled the trigger.

212
00:09:23,014 --> 00:09:25,1
(gasps, exhales weakly)

213
00:09:29,065 --> 00:09:31,3
(siren wails in distance)

214
00:09:42,037 --> 00:09:44,2
(helicopter whirring)

215
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,6
♪♪

216
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,2
(indistinct chatter)

217
00:09:53,042 --> 00:09:56,1
(siren whooping)

218
00:10:03,056 --> 00:10:05,6
(camera beeping, clicking)

219
00:10:05,089 --> 00:10:08,4
(sirens whooping)

220
00:10:11,036 --> 00:10:13,2
MAN: Want to hear
what I've got so far?

221
00:10:15,078 --> 00:10:17,7
Lieutenant said
this is my case.

222
00:10:17,091 --> 00:10:20,5
Yeah, Chloe,
it is your case,

223
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:22,2
but try not to take
too much time.

224
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:23,4
It's an easy one.

225
00:10:23,062 --> 00:10:24,9
That's our bad guy.

226
00:10:25,012 --> 00:10:27,8
Eddie Deacon, he's
a low-level drug dealer.

227
00:10:28,004 --> 00:10:29,3
I found these in his pocket,

228
00:10:29,054 --> 00:10:31,2
and I found this
in Delilah's purse,

229
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,8
so obviously drug-related.

230
00:10:33,009 --> 00:10:34,9
She probably owed him
a bunch of cash or something.

231
00:10:35,013 --> 00:10:37,2
She's not exactly selling out
stadiums these days.

232
00:10:37,047 --> 00:10:38,4
How do you know
he's low-level?

233
00:10:38,063 --> 00:10:40,5
Look at his car.

234
00:10:40,076 --> 00:10:42,2
Did you look at his watch?

235
00:10:42,043 --> 00:10:43,4
That thing ain't cheap.

236
00:10:43,068 --> 00:10:45,2
MAN:
It's probably fake.

237
00:10:45,047 --> 00:10:47,2
Look...

238
00:10:47,048 --> 00:10:50,2
there's gonna be a lot of
attention on this one, Chloe.

239
00:10:50,048 --> 00:10:52,2
I wouldn't pick at it too hard.

240
00:10:52,048 --> 00:10:53,9
Not after Palmetto Street.

241
00:10:54,015 --> 00:10:56,9
I asked for this case
because of Palmetto Street, Dan.

242
00:10:58,099 --> 00:11:01,2
So, anyway, any witnesses?

243
00:11:01,049 --> 00:11:04,0
LUCIFER:
Lucifer Morningstar.

244
00:11:04,024 --> 00:11:06,7
"Lucifer
Morningstar"?

245
00:11:06,091 --> 00:11:09,7
Is that, uh,
a stage name or something?

246
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,6
(chuckles)
God-given, I'm afraid.

247
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:12,8
You know,

248
00:11:13,004 --> 00:11:13,9
you look familiar.

249
00:11:14,013 --> 00:11:15,1
Have we met before?

250
00:11:15,034 --> 00:11:17,8
Yeah, five minutes ago.

251
00:11:18,009 --> 00:11:19,6
And I'm asking the questions.

252
00:11:19,088 --> 00:11:21,9
Talk to me about your
relationship with the victim.

253
00:11:22,018 --> 00:11:24,3
Well, she used to work here
a few years back.

254
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:26,8
I would occasionally
accompany her while she sang.

255
00:11:27,002 --> 00:11:30,2
Then she became a big star and
someone decided to end her life.

256
00:11:30,048 --> 00:11:31,9
Do you know the shooter?

257
00:11:32,010 --> 00:11:33,6
No, but we did have
an interesting little chat

258
00:11:33,081 --> 00:11:35,7
just before he kicked off.

259
00:11:35,098 --> 00:11:37,8
