00:40:20,008 --> 00:40:22,0
aren't you?

1034
00:40:22,025 --> 00:40:23,5
(sighs)

1035
00:40:25,013 --> 00:40:27,0
- What happened with Jimmy?
- Jimmy?

1036
00:40:27,021 --> 00:40:29,5
Jimmy got what he deserved.

1037
00:40:29,072 --> 00:40:31,3
Hmm?

1038
00:40:32,084 --> 00:40:35,1
Well, I'm pretty sure
I'd be dead

1039
00:40:35,039 --> 00:40:36,6
if you hadn't helped me,
so...

1040
00:40:36,085 --> 00:40:38,8
thank you.

1041
00:40:39,010 --> 00:40:40,8
Sorry, what was that?
That last bit.

1042
00:40:41,006 --> 00:40:42,7
I didn't quite
get that.

1043
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:45,5
Thank you.

1044
00:40:46,069 --> 00:40:48,6
You're welcome.

1045
00:40:48,090 --> 00:40:50,5
And, besides, you know,

1046
00:40:50,078 --> 00:40:52,7
you're far too interesting
to let die.

1047
00:40:54,041 --> 00:40:56,3
You saved my life
because I'm interesting?

1048
00:40:56,058 --> 00:40:58,4
Wildly irritating as well,
but yes.

1049
00:40:58,062 --> 00:40:59,5
(chuckles softly)

1050
00:41:02,008 --> 00:41:03,5
So what now?

1051
00:41:03,079 --> 00:41:05,0
Well, I mean,
I've obviously proven myself

1052
00:41:05,025 --> 00:41:06,4
to be an invaluable
crime-fighting tool.

1053
00:41:06,063 --> 00:41:08,5
You're a pariah
in the department.

1054
00:41:08,071 --> 00:41:10,0
I think this could be the start

1055
00:41:10,021 --> 00:41:11,0
of a beautiful friendship.
Don't you?

1056
00:41:11,022 --> 00:41:13,0
Who the hell are you?

1057
00:41:13,022 --> 00:41:15,2
I told you, I'm...

1058
00:41:15,047 --> 00:41:16,8
Lucifer!

1059
00:41:17,089 --> 00:41:20,0
Uh, yes. Hello, child.

1060
00:41:20,027 --> 00:41:22,1
Um, just... Why don't you save

1061
00:41:22,039 --> 00:41:24,0
some of this unpleasantness
for your mother, yeah?

1062
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:25,2
- (groans)
- Ooh.

1063
00:41:25,048 --> 00:41:27,2
- Sorry.
- Oh.

1064
00:41:27,048 --> 00:41:29,4
- God.
- Are you hurt?

1065
00:41:29,061 --> 00:41:30,9
I'm okay.

1066
00:41:31,011 --> 00:41:32,7
LUCIFER: Right.
Well, I'd stay for

1067
00:41:32,090 --> 00:41:34,5
the family reunion,
but it's giving me terrible IBS.

1068
00:41:34,078 --> 00:41:36,9
So, look forward
to seeing you soon, Chloe.

1069
00:41:37,020 --> 00:41:39,0
- I don't.
- Bye, now.

1070
00:41:39,029 --> 00:41:40,4
Glad you're not dead.

1071
00:41:43,046 --> 00:41:46,7
♪ Always something
before the late night ♪

1072
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:49,0
♪ Around the corner,
there's always ♪

1073
00:41:49,025 --> 00:41:51,4
(distorting):
♪ Something waiting for you... ♪

1074
00:41:51,063 --> 00:41:53,8
(groans)
Bloody hell.

1075
00:41:59,031 --> 00:42:01,4
What do you want
from me?

1076
00:42:01,064 --> 00:42:03,9
I've been watching you, Lucifer.

1077
00:42:04,019 --> 00:42:05,9
- You perv.
- And I'm not sure

1078
00:42:06,015 --> 00:42:07,5
I like what I see.

1079
00:42:07,077 --> 00:42:10,2
You're showing restraint, mercy.

1080
00:42:10,048 --> 00:42:13,4
You scared I'm turning my back
on the dark side, bro?

1081
00:42:13,065 --> 00:42:17,2
Lucifer, there is a balance here
that we must maintain.

1082
00:42:17,045 --> 00:42:19,8
I strongly suggest you do
what I told you to do

1083
00:42:20,003 --> 00:42:21,2
and go back to Hell.

1084
00:42:21,049 --> 00:42:24,2
Don't threaten me, Amenadiel.

1085
00:42:24,050 --> 00:42:26,9
I mean, you don't want
to start a war.

1086
00:42:27,012 --> 00:42:30,1
I would love a war.

1087
00:42:30,038 --> 00:42:32,3
(chuckling)

1088
00:42:32,051 --> 00:42:35,1
Oh, Luci.

1089
00:42:35,038 --> 00:42:38,7
My hatred for you grows stronger
with every visit.

1090
00:42:38,097 --> 00:42:42,0
Well, I wouldn't have it
any other way, pal.

1091
00:42:42,022 --> 00:42:45,1
I look forward
to eating your heart one day.

1092
00:42:45,031 --> 00:42:46,6
Peace.

1093
00:42:51,069 --> 00:42:54,7
(wings flapping)

1094
00:42:54,094 --> 00:42:56,8
Ugh.

1095
00:43:05,045 --> 00:43:07,3
I sense your
disapproval, Maze.

1096
00:43:07,058 --> 00:43:09,3
What is it?

1097
00:43:09,058 --> 00:43:14,8
I just can't understand
why you would save a human life.

1098
00:43:15,009 --> 00:43:17,3
Well, there's...
something different about her

1099
00:43:17,055 --> 00:43:19,9
that I don't quite understand,
and it vexes me.

1100
00:43:20,018 --> 00:43:22,5
Maybe it's not her
that's different.

1101
00:43:22,072 --> 00:43:25,0
(chuckles) Is this
where I'm supposed to ask,

1102
00:43:25,027 --> 00:43:26,8
"Whatever do you mean?"

1103
00:43:27,006 --> 00:43:29,5
I'm worried the humans
are rubbing off on you.

1104
00:43:29,073 --> 00:43:31,8
Stop caring.

1105
00:43:33,007 --> 00:43:34,9
You're the Devil.

1106
00:43:37,049 --> 00:43:39,2
Yes, I am.

1107
00:43:39,045 --> 00:43:41,2
♪♪

1108
00:43:52,088 --> 00:43:54,8
Okay. Right.
Uh...

1109
00:43:55,009 --> 00:43:57,0
Here's the deal.
We can have as much naked

1110
00:43:57,026 --> 00:43:59,2
cuddle time
as you desire, but...

1111
00:43:59,043 --> 00:44:01,3
you're gonna have
to listen to me, too.

1112
00:44:01,059 --> 00:44:04,6
There's a few things that
I'd like to discuss with you.

1113
00:44:04,089 --> 00:44:08,0
You know, just a...
an existential dilemma or two.

1114
00:44:08,023 --> 00:44:09,2
Deal?

1115
00:44:09,044 --> 00:44:11,4
- Yes.
- Lovely.

1116
00:44:11,060 --> 00:44:14,7
♪ Oh, no, there ain't
no rest for the wicked ♪

1117
00:44:14,098 --> 00:44:18,2
♪ Until we close
our eyes for good... ♪

